From 0a5a0713b44ec9cb04e2473b1148404a42bd6ec6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 22:53:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: add gallery-dl metadata fallback for Instagram posts
 without cookies
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

yt-dlp requires Instagram cookies for metadata; without them it returns nothing
(author=None, body=0 chars). gallery-dl was already working for image URLs on
the same posts, so use it as a metadata source too.

Extraction priority order:
1. yt-dlp (best — has comment support, needs cookies)
2. gallery-dl -j (works on public posts without auth, no comments)
3. instaloader (comment-only fallback, needs session file)

_ytdlp_metadata: renamed from _instaloader_metadata, returns {} cleanly when
  yt-dlp produces no info.json so the fallback chain triggers.
_gallery_dl_metadata: new — runs gallery-dl -j, parses first item's metadata
  dict for caption (description), handle (username), display name (fullname),
  date, shortcode, likes.
_instaloader_first_owner_comment: accepts optional owner_handle param so the
  gallery-dl path can pass the handle it already discovered.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01G3CevLYb6JPcyW363NyKGN
